<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>How to Plan a Post-Wedding Brunch</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css" />
</head>
<body>

  <header class="hero-brplanning">
    <div class="hero-overlay-brplanning"></div>
    <div class="hero-content-brplanning">
      <h1>How to Plan a Post-Wedding Brunch</h1>
      <p>Elegant tips for a relaxing, luxurious day-after celebration</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="step-section-brplanning">
    <div class="step-card-brplanning">
      <img src="https://www.zap-store.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/Golding-Redding_11.05.19_167.jpg" alt="Delegate the Planning" />
      <h2>1. Delegate the Planning</h2>
      <p>Share the load with a planner, your parents, or someone close. Wake up relaxed and walk into a beautiful brunch that's already ready for you.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step-card-brplanning">
      <img src="https://i.etsystatic.com/8071805/r/il/4707e8/6324452801/il_1080xN.6324452801_fnix.jpg" alt="Select a Time" />
      <h2>2. Select a Time</h2>
      <p>Pick a time like 10am–12pm so guests can pack, check out, and drop by for a lovely farewell meal.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step-card-brplanning">
      <img src="https://healthyway.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/pexels-soner-gorkem-6119578.jpg" alt="Create the Guest List" />
      <h2>3. Create the Guest List</h2>
      <p>Keep it intimate or invite everyone—it’s your call. Just be clear on who’s invited and avoid confusion with private spaces or invitation inserts.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step-card-brplanning">
      <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/24/2b/c8/242bc8b420c9986bf4ebaf31d528bfca.jpg" alt="Plan the Menu" />
      <h2>4. Plan the Menu</h2>
      <p>Serve what you love—pastries, omelettes, even donuts! Let your food reflect your taste or local flavors for a personal touch.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step-card-brplanning">
      <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/24/2b/c8/242bc8b420c9986bf4ebaf31d528bfca.jpg" alt="Plan the Menu" />
      <h2>5. Decide on a Location</h2>
      <p>Choose a cozy hotel, charming restaurant, or a private home. Make sure it's accessible for guests and offers a relaxed setting.</p>
      
    </div>
    
    <div class="step-card-brplanning">
      <img src="https://www.brides.com/thmb/ppiMjduGi2jOsZsm7GFgkd6QDAA=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/guests-at-rehearsal-dinner-recirc-adovasio-12-18-8370d2563e3e4965a5788552123aa5ea.jpg" alt="Choose a Dress" />
      <h2>6. Choose a Dress</h2>
      <p>Select a stylish yet comfortable outfit for your brunch. This is the perfect opportunity to showcase your taste in fashion without compromising on ease.</p>
      
    </div>
</section>
</body>
</html>